{"video_id": "yp6RiH3xOYA", "title": "2015-10-13 | SB 3.17.19 | HG Amitasana Dasa", "speaker": "HG Amitasana Dasa", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yp6RiH3xOYA", "duration": 1679, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 20.080000000000002, "text": " Reading from Srimad Bhagavatam, Canto No. 3, Chapter No. 17, Text No. 19."}, {"start": 30.0, "end": 48.66, "text": " Translation and purport by His Divine Grace A.C. Bhaktivedanta Swamishlaprabhupada."}, {"start": 50.04, "end": 50.760000000000005, "text": " Translation."}, {"start": 51.44, "end": 57.260000000000005, "text": " The elder child, Rinukashipu, was unafraid of death from anyone within the three worlds"}, {"start": 57.260000000000005, "end": 59.980000000000004, "text": " because he received a benediction from Lakshman."}, {"start": 60.0, "end": 64.5, "text": " He was proud and puffed up due to his benediction"}, {"start": 64.5, "end": 68.92, "text": " and was able to bring all three planetary systems under his control."}, {"start": 70.58, "end": 71.38, "text": " Purport."}, {"start": 72.54, "end": 75.18, "text": " As will be revealed in later chapters,"}, {"start": 75.5, "end": 79.78, "text": " Rinukashipu underwent severe austerity and penance to satisfy Brahma"}, {"start": 79.78, "end": 83.34, "text": " and thus received a benediction of immortality."}, {"start": 84.48, "end": 89.94, "text": " Actually, it is impossible even for Lord Brahma to give anyone the benediction of being immortal."}, {"start": 90.54, "end": 93.68, "text": " But indirectly, Rinukashipu received the benediction"}, {"start": 93.68, "end": 97.36, "text": " that no one within this material world would be able to kill him."}, {"start": 98.36, "end": 101.96000000000001, "text": " In other words, because he originally came from the abode of Vaikuntha,"}, {"start": 102.18, "end": 105.4, "text": " he was not to be killed by anyone within this material world."}, {"start": 107.66, "end": 110.46000000000001, "text": " The Lord desired to appear himself to kill him."}, {"start": 111.6, "end": 114.8, "text": " One may be very proud of his material advancement in knowledge,"}, {"start": 114.8, "end": 118.68, "text": " but he cannot be immune to the four principles of material existence,"}, {"start": 119.38, "end": 119.72, "text": " namely,"}, {"start": 120.0, "end": 120.26, "text": " birth,"}, {"start": 120.66, "end": 121.08, "text": " death,"}, {"start": 121.4, "end": 121.92, "text": " old age,"}, {"start": 122.12, "end": 122.66, "text": " and disease."}, {"start": 123.88, "end": 127.38, "text": " It was Lord's plan to teach people that even Rinukashipu,"}, {"start": 127.52, "end": 129.64, "text": " who was so powerful and strongly built,"}, {"start": 130.28, "end": 133.8, "text": " could not live more than his destined duration of life."}, {"start": 135.14, "end": 138.2, "text": " One may become as strong and puffed up as Rinukashipu"}, {"start": 138.2, "end": 140.52, "text": " and bring under his control all the three worlds,"}, {"start": 140.52, "end": 144.12, "text": " but there is no possibility of continuing life eternally"}, {"start": 144.12, "end": 147.24, "text": " or keeping the conquered booty forever."}, {"start": 148.74, "end": 149.82, "text": " So many emperors,"}, {"start": 150.0, "end": 151.34, "text": " who have ascended to Paa,"}, {"start": 151.38, "end": 154.34, "text": " and they are now lost in oblivion,"}, {"start": 154.88, "end": 157.98, "text": " that is the history of the world."}, {"start": 157.98, "end": 159.96, "text": " Thus ends the Bhagavad Gita."}, {"start": 159.96, "end": 161.98, "text": " So here in this verse,"}, {"start": 162.64, "end": 163.88, "text": " Rinukashipu,"}, {"start": 164.36, "end": 167.6, "text": " who had received a benediction from Lord Brahma,"}, {"start": 170.96, "end": 172.96, "text": " and the benediction was"}, {"start": 172.96, "end": 178.32, "text": " that no one within this material world would be able to kill him."}, {"start": 178.32, "end": 184.32, "text": " So Prabhupada mentions that although Brahma cannot give the benediction of"}, {"start": 184.32, "end": 190.32, "text": " Trinakashrupa being immortal, but indirectly he got that benediction."}, {"start": 190.32, "end": 201.32, "text": " And because of the benediction that he cannot be killed by anyone in the material world,"}, {"start": 201.32, "end": 205.32, "text": " he was proud and puffed up."}, {"start": 205.32, "end": 217.32, "text": " And was able to bring all three planetary systems under his control."}, {"start": 217.32, "end": 227.32, "text": " He was also unafraid of death from anyone within the three worlds."}, {"start": 227.32, "end": 235.32, "text": " So,"}, {"start": 235.32, "end": 241.32, "text": " given Trinakashrupa here,"}, {"start": 241.32, "end": 248.32, "text": " unlike the qualities which we should be aspiring for,"}, {"start": 248.32, "end": 252.32, "text": " the quality of being humble,"}, {"start": 252.32, "end": 255.32, "text": " the quality of being tolerant,"}, {"start": 255.32, "end": 262.32, "text": " the quality of being subservient to the devotees,"}, {"start": 262.32, "end": 265.32, "text": " to always consider oneself meek and humble,"}, {"start": 265.32, "end": 271.32, "text": " unlike that, because Trinakashrupa was puffed up,"}, {"start": 271.32, "end": 277.32, "text": " he was embodiment of just the opposite of these qualities."}, {"start": 277.32, "end": 281.32, "text": " Unafraid of death."}, {"start": 281.32, "end": 292.32, "text": " One time there was a lady,"}, {"start": 292.32, "end": 294.32, "text": " she had in her home,"}, {"start": 294.32, "end": 302.32, "text": " her grandchild who had come from a distant place for a vacation."}, {"start": 302.32, "end": 306.32, "text": " So every morning when the child would get up,"}, {"start": 306.32, "end": 313.32, "text": " he would come to his grandmom and she would be writing something."}, {"start": 313.32, "end": 315.32, "text": " Maybe she was an author or something."}, {"start": 315.32, "end": 320.32, "text": " She would be always writing something."}, {"start": 320.32, "end": 322.32, "text": " Always with a paper and,"}, {"start": 322.32, "end": 327.32, "text": " and she would write with a pencil."}, {"start": 327.32, "end": 329.32, "text": " So one day this child,"}, {"start": 329.32, "end": 332.32, "text": " this small child became inquisitive and asked,"}, {"start": 332.32, "end": 335.32, "text": " what are you writing?"}, {"start": 335.32, "end": 338.32, "text": " Is it about me?"}, {"start": 338.32, "end": 344.32, "text": " Is it about us?"}, {"start": 344.32, "end": 347.32, "text": " So the lady said,"}, {"start": 347.32, "end": 350.32, "text": " what I am writing is relatively unimportant."}, {"start": 350.32, "end": 356.32, "text": " But since you have asked the question,"}, {"start": 356.32, "end": 362.32, "text": " let me tell you that this pencil with which I am writing,"}, {"start": 362.32, "end": 366.32, "text": " whatever I am writing,"}, {"start": 366.32, "end": 369.32, "text": " it is playing a very, very important role."}, {"start": 369.32, "end": 376.32, "text": " And before you leave,"}, {"start": 376.32, "end": 378.32, "text": " after the vacation gets over,"}, {"start": 378.32, "end": 384.32, "text": " I will gift you this pencil."}, {"start": 384.32, "end": 386.32, "text": " So the child,"}, {"start": 386.32, "end": 388.32, "text": " you know, he had been also writing with pencil,"}, {"start": 388.32, "end": 390.32, "text": " so he was a little surprised."}, {"start": 390.32, "end": 394.32, "text": " What's the big deal about a pencil?"}, {"start": 394.32, "end": 397.32, "text": " How is it different from the rest of pencils"}, {"start": 397.32, "end": 402.32, "text": " which is available in the market so easily?"}, {"start": 402.32, "end": 404.32, "text": " He said, I will give you this pencil"}, {"start": 404.32, "end": 407.32, "text": " and I want you to imbibe,"}, {"start": 407.32, "end": 410.32, "text": " you will imbibe the five qualities"}, {"start": 410.32, "end": 412.32, "text": " what you see in this pencil"}, {"start": 412.32, "end": 414.32, "text": " for the rest of your life."}, {"start": 414.32, "end": 416.32, "text": " And if you do that,"}, {"start": 416.32, "end": 421.32, "text": " you will become a great man."}, {"start": 421.32, "end": 424.32, "text": " So again the child was somehow intrigued"}, {"start": 424.32, "end": 425.32, "text": " what the mother is,"}, {"start": 425.32, "end": 428.32, "text": " what the grandmother is trying to tell."}, {"start": 428.32, "end": 429.32, "text": " So she says,"}, {"start": 429.32, "end": 432.32, "text": " the first quality in the pencil,"}, {"start": 432.32, "end": 435.32, "text": " you see it is an ordinary pencil,"}, {"start": 435.32, "end": 437.32, "text": " but the pencil,"}, {"start": 437.32, "end": 439.32, "text": " just remembers"}, {"start": 439.32, "end": 445.32, "text": " that there is a hand guiding it."}, {"start": 445.32, "end": 446.32, "text": " Using a pencil,"}, {"start": 446.32, "end": 448.32, "text": " a writer, an author might write"}, {"start": 448.32, "end": 449.32, "text": " some wonderful text"}, {"start": 449.32, "end": 451.32, "text": " like Shakespeare wrote,"}, {"start": 451.32, "end": 455.32, "text": " wonderful, you know,"}, {"start": 455.32, "end": 458.32, "text": " whatever his writings, his poems,"}, {"start": 458.32, "end": 463.32, "text": " so famous he is for all his writings,"}, {"start": 463.32, "end": 466.32, "text": " he would have used a pen or a pencil to write it."}, {"start": 467.32, "end": 470.32, "text": " But the credit goes to the Shakespeare."}, {"start": 470.32, "end": 472.32, "text": " Although,"}, {"start": 472.32, "end": 474.32, "text": " what was literally written in the paper"}, {"start": 474.32, "end": 476.32, "text": " was written by a pen,"}, {"start": 476.32, "end": 479.32, "text": " but the pen or a pencil never took any credit."}, {"start": 479.32, "end": 482.32, "text": " It was always conscious,"}, {"start": 482.32, "end": 483.32, "text": " had it been conscious,"}, {"start": 483.32, "end": 485.32, "text": " assuming that the pen is conscious"}, {"start": 485.32, "end": 486.32, "text": " or a pencil is conscious,"}, {"start": 486.32, "end": 489.32, "text": " it is very, very clear"}, {"start": 489.32, "end": 493.32, "text": " that I am being used."}, {"start": 493.32, "end": 496.32, "text": " Something was being used,"}, {"start": 496.32, "end": 498.32, "text": " something wonderful may come up,"}, {"start": 498.32, "end": 502.32, "text": " but it will never ever even think of taking a credit."}, {"start": 502.32, "end": 503.32, "text": " So likewise,"}, {"start": 503.32, "end": 505.32, "text": " a pencil always remembers"}, {"start": 505.32, "end": 511.32, "text": " that there is a hand guiding it."}, {"start": 511.32, "end": 512.3199999999999, "text": " Here,"}, {"start": 512.3199999999999, "end": 513.3199999999999, "text": " Himata Shubha, we see,"}, {"start": 513.3199999999999, "end": 514.3199999999999, "text": " is getting puffed up,"}, {"start": 514.3199999999999, "end": 516.3199999999999, "text": " is proud,"}, {"start": 516.3199999999999, "end": 520.3199999999999, "text": " because he is not able to see the hand."}, {"start": 520.3199999999999, "end": 522.3199999999999, "text": " Even when we become proud,"}, {"start": 522.3199999999999, "end": 525.3199999999999, "text": " or when we achieve something,"}, {"start": 525.32, "end": 527.32, "text": " or when we accomplish something,"}, {"start": 527.32, "end": 529.32, "text": " or when we do something big"}, {"start": 529.32, "end": 531.32, "text": " in the service of the Lord,"}, {"start": 531.32, "end": 534.32, "text": " unless we remember that we are just"}, {"start": 534.32, "end": 535.32, "text": " nimitta mātra,"}, {"start": 535.32, "end": 538.32, "text": " we are just an instrument in the hand of the Lord,"}, {"start": 538.32, "end": 541.32, "text": " actually all credit goes to the Lord,"}, {"start": 541.32, "end": 543.32, "text": " unless we consciously remember,"}, {"start": 543.32, "end": 548.32, "text": " unless we consciously give due credit to the Lord."}, {"start": 548.32, "end": 553.32, "text": " sarvasya cāhaṁ vidhi-saṇi viṣṭo matasme ter jñānaṁ apok."}, {"start": 553.32, "end": 554.32, "text": " The ideas, the thought,"}, {"start": 554.32, "end": 559.32, "text": " the inspiration came from the Lord."}, {"start": 559.32, "end": 561.32, "text": " Unless we remember that,"}, {"start": 561.32, "end": 567.32, "text": " we will also become proud."}, {"start": 567.32, "end": 568.32, "text": " So here we are saying,"}, {"start": 568.32, "end": 569.32, "text": " Himata Shubha is proud"}, {"start": 569.32, "end": 571.32, "text": " because he is totally oblivious of"}, {"start": 571.32, "end": 574.32, "text": " that he is amsa of the Lord."}, {"start": 574.32, "end": 576.32, "text": " The Lord is the supreme controller."}, {"start": 576.32, "end": 580.32, "text": " Because he has got three planetary systems under his control,"}, {"start": 580.32, "end": 582.32, "text": " he is thinking he is great,"}, {"start": 582.32, "end": 584.32, "text": " he is immortal."}, {"start": 584.32, "end": 589.32, "text": " Nobody can touch him."}, {"start": 589.32, "end": 591.32, "text": " But a devotee knowing that,"}, {"start": 591.32, "end": 593.32, "text": " in fact in the fourth chapter,"}, {"start": 593.32, "end": 594.32, "text": " twentieth verse,"}, {"start": 594.32, "end": 597.32, "text": " Kṛṣṇa mentions,"}, {"start": 597.32, "end": 601.32, "text": " Prabhupāda explains that a devotee,"}, {"start": 601.32, "end": 603.32, "text": " when he does anything,"}, {"start": 603.32, "end": 606.32, "text": " he is not attached to the results"}, {"start": 606.32, "end": 608.32, "text": " because he knows whatever he is doing"}, {"start": 608.32, "end": 613.32, "text": " is done by the Lord."}, {"start": 613.32, "end": 615.32, "text": " Why the devotee is not attached to the results,"}, {"start": 615.32, "end": 618.32, "text": " it is not some artificial imposition in the mind,"}, {"start": 618.32, "end": 620.32, "text": " because of this consciousness that"}, {"start": 620.32, "end": 624.32, "text": " it is being done by the Lord through him."}, {"start": 624.32, "end": 627.32, "text": " He is just an instrument,"}, {"start": 627.32, "end": 630.32, "text": " just like the pencil,"}, {"start": 630.32, "end": 633.32, "text": " just an instrument."}, {"start": 633.32, "end": 639.32, "text": " The second quality of the pencil is,"}, {"start": 639.32, "end": 642.32, "text": " it learns to bear,"}, {"start": 642.32, "end": 645.32, "text": " it learns to bear pains and sorrows."}, {"start": 645.32, "end": 651.32, "text": " After every few hours of writing,"}, {"start": 651.32, "end": 653.32, "text": " the person who is holding the pencil,"}, {"start": 653.32, "end": 655.32, "text": " the grandmother would use a sharpener"}, {"start": 655.32, "end": 657.32, "text": " and sharpen the pencil."}, {"start": 657.32, "end": 660.32, "text": " And although the pencil may go through some pain,"}, {"start": 660.32, "end": 663.32, "text": " when you are, so to say, being sharpened,"}, {"start": 663.32, "end": 665.32, "text": " but after that pain,"}, {"start": 665.32, "end": 668.32, "text": " after that so-called suffering,"}, {"start": 668.32, "end": 671.32, "text": " the pencils become sharp."}, {"start": 672.32, "end": 675.32, "text": " And it drives better."}, {"start": 675.32, "end": 680.32, "text": " So likewise, a devotee also,"}, {"start": 680.32, "end": 682.32, "text": " with his Kṛṣṇa consciousness,"}, {"start": 682.32, "end": 688.32, "text": " is willing to go through pains and pleasures,"}, {"start": 688.32, "end": 690.32, "text": " sorrows,"}, {"start": 690.32, "end": 694.32, "text": " knowing that the Lord is his well-wisher,"}, {"start": 694.32, "end": 697.32, "text": " knowing that Avashya Rakshabhi Kṛṣṇa,"}, {"start": 697.32, "end": 701.32, "text": " knowing that the Lord is in control of my life,"}, {"start": 701.32, "end": 704.32, "text": " knowing that the Lord is taking me through all this"}, {"start": 704.32, "end": 707.32, "text": " to make me a better devotee,"}, {"start": 707.32, "end": 709.32, "text": " to make me more dependent on Him,"}, {"start": 709.32, "end": 712.32, "text": " same as the case being"}, {"start": 712.32, "end": 713.32, "text": " for Kunti Mahārāj,"}, {"start": 713.32, "end": 718.32, "text": " the Lord gives us more and more troubles."}, {"start": 718.32, "end": 720.32, "text": " Unlike Rina Kashyapu here,"}, {"start": 720.32, "end": 722.32, "text": " who is trying to ward off all troubles"}, {"start": 722.32, "end": 724.32, "text": " of birth, death, old age, disease,"}, {"start": 724.32, "end": 728.32, "text": " by becoming immortal,"}, {"start": 728.32, "end": 729.32, "text": " a devotee of the Lord"}, {"start": 729.32, "end": 732.32, "text": " does not make such endeavours."}, {"start": 732.32, "end": 739.32, "text": " He is rather endeavouring to be dependent on the Lord."}, {"start": 739.32, "end": 744.32, "text": " Knowing the dangers in the material world,"}, {"start": 744.32, "end": 746.32, "text": " this material world which Kṛṣṇa says is"}, {"start": 746.32, "end": 747.32, "text": " duḥ khālaya māśāśvatam,"}, {"start": 747.32, "end": 750.32, "text": " rather than investing all his time and energy"}, {"start": 750.32, "end": 752.32, "text": " making this place a wonderful place"}, {"start": 752.32, "end": 754.32, "text": " to stay in comfortably eternally,"}, {"start": 754.32, "end": 757.32, "text": " realising that it is temporary"}, {"start": 757.32, "end": 758.32, "text": " and it is a place of misery,"}, {"start": 758.32, "end": 760.32, "text": " he invests his time and energy"}, {"start": 760.32, "end": 762.32, "text": " in becoming conscious of the Lord,"}, {"start": 762.32, "end": 765.32, "text": " dependent on the Lord."}, {"start": 765.32, "end": 768.32, "text": " Even if he goes through some pains and pleasures,"}, {"start": 768.32, "end": 769.32, "text": " he takes it in stride,"}, {"start": 769.32, "end": 770.32, "text": " learns the lessons,"}, {"start": 770.32, "end": 773.32, "text": " depends on Kṛṣṇa more and more,"}, {"start": 773.32, "end": 777.32, "text": " and becomes a better devotee."}, {"start": 777.32, "end": 779.32, "text": " So the pencil also,"}, {"start": 779.32, "end": 780.32, "text": " when it is sharpened,"}, {"start": 780.32, "end": 782.32, "text": " it does not rebel."}, {"start": 782.32, "end": 784.32, "text": " It allows to be sharpened,"}, {"start": 784.32, "end": 786.32, "text": " although it goes through some pain,"}, {"start": 786.32, "end": 787.32, "text": " although it gets shortened,"}, {"start": 787.32, "end": 791.32, "text": " but in the process,"}, {"start": 791.32, "end": 793.32, "text": " it becomes better,"}, {"start": 793.32, "end": 795.32, "text": " better in writing."}, {"start": 795.32, "end": 798.32, "text": " The third quality of a pencil is"}, {"start": 798.32, "end": 802.32, "text": " when you write with a pencil,"}, {"start": 802.32, "end": 806.32, "text": " it allows you to rub"}, {"start": 806.32, "end": 809.32, "text": " in case you have made a mistake."}, {"start": 809.32, "end": 815.32, "text": " This is also a good quality of a devotee,"}, {"start": 815.32, "end": 816.32, "text": " where a devotee,"}, {"start": 816.32, "end": 820.32, "text": " unlike what is being depicted"}, {"start": 820.32, "end": 822.32, "text": " by Hruna Kashyapu,"}, {"start": 822.32, "end": 823.32, "text": " the qualities,"}, {"start": 823.32, "end": 826.32, "text": " a devotee is humble"}, {"start": 826.32, "end": 833.32, "text": " and he allows to be corrected."}, {"start": 833.32, "end": 836.32, "text": " If suppose he comes across instructions"}, {"start": 836.32, "end": 839.32, "text": " in the Bhagavad Gita, Bhagavatam,"}, {"start": 839.32, "end": 843.32, "text": " and he realises that he is not behaving properly"}, {"start": 843.32, "end": 845.32, "text": " or the qualities what he is exhibiting"}, {"start": 845.32, "end": 847.32, "text": " is not in line with"}, {"start": 847.32, "end": 849.32, "text": " the qualities of a saintly person,"}, {"start": 849.32, "end": 851.32, "text": " or someone gives a feedback,"}, {"start": 851.32, "end": 853.32, "text": " if a person is pavdaad,"}, {"start": 853.32, "end": 854.32, "text": " he says,"}, {"start": 854.32, "end": 856.32, "text": " how dare you tell me?"}, {"start": 856.32, "end": 860.32, "text": " What do you think of yourself?"}, {"start": 860.32, "end": 863.32, "text": " Who do you think you are?"}, {"start": 863.32, "end": 865.32, "text": " Whereas a devotee,"}, {"start": 865.32, "end": 866.32, "text": " just like the pencil,"}, {"start": 866.32, "end": 868.32, "text": " allows itself to be rubbed"}, {"start": 868.32, "end": 869.32, "text": " in case you have made a mistake."}, {"start": 869.32, "end": 874.32, "text": " We all make mistakes to arrest human."}, {"start": 874.32, "end": 876.32, "text": " Even with good intentions,"}, {"start": 876.32, "end": 877.32, "text": " if we go about leading our lives,"}, {"start": 877.32, "end": 882.32, "text": " still we will make mistakes."}, {"start": 882.32, "end": 883.32, "text": " We all have blind spots."}, {"start": 883.32, "end": 885.32, "text": " We don't know that we don't know."}, {"start": 885.32, "end": 886.32, "text": " Many times,"}, {"start": 886.32, "end": 888.32, "text": " the mistakes will be pointed out to us."}, {"start": 888.32, "end": 890.32, "text": " Our behaviours will be corrected."}, {"start": 890.32, "end": 891.32, "text": " Somebody senior would point out that"}, {"start": 891.32, "end": 893.32, "text": " this is not the way to act."}, {"start": 893.32, "end": 894.32, "text": " This is not the way to behave."}, {"start": 894.32, "end": 896.32, "text": " This is not the way to speak."}, {"start": 896.32, "end": 898.32, "text": " And if you are not humble,"}, {"start": 898.32, "end": 902.32, "text": " then we will rebel."}, {"start": 902.32, "end": 903.32, "text": " We will not take correction and stuff."}, {"start": 903.32, "end": 907.32, "text": " We will not be open to feedback."}, {"start": 907.32, "end": 909.32, "text": " We will get angry."}, {"start": 909.32, "end": 911.32, "text": " We will be hatred."}, {"start": 911.32, "end": 912.32, "text": " So like a pencil,"}, {"start": 912.32, "end": 914.32, "text": " it allows to be corrected."}, {"start": 914.32, "end": 916.32, "text": " Yes, mistake has happened."}, {"start": 916.32, "end": 918.32, "text": " One takes the feedback,"}, {"start": 918.32, "end": 920.32, "text": " sees if there is a grain of truth,"}, {"start": 920.32, "end": 921.32, "text": " and then corrects himself"}, {"start": 921.32, "end": 924.32, "text": " and move forward."}, {"start": 924.32, "end": 927.32, "text": " So this is the third quality of a pencil."}, {"start": 927.32, "end": 930.32, "text": " The fourth quality is,"}, {"start": 930.32, "end": 931.32, "text": " although we may see pencil"}, {"start": 931.32, "end": 932.32, "text": " different designs these days"}, {"start": 932.32, "end": 934.32, "text": " in the marketplace,"}, {"start": 934.32, "end": 935.32, "text": " different colours,"}, {"start": 935.32, "end": 936.32, "text": " different designs."}, {"start": 936.32, "end": 937.32, "text": " These days,"}, {"start": 937.32, "end": 939.32, "text": " let's say if Chota Bean is a serial coming,"}, {"start": 939.32, "end": 940.32, "text": " you will have a pencil with Chota Bean"}, {"start": 940.32, "end": 942.32, "text": " cartoon on top of it."}, {"start": 942.32, "end": 944.32, "text": " All kinds of designs are there."}, {"start": 944.32, "end": 946.32, "text": " So much innovation has happened"}, {"start": 946.32, "end": 947.32, "text": " to make it attractive"}, {"start": 947.32, "end": 949.32, "text": " so that children fall for it"}, {"start": 949.32, "end": 950.32, "text": " and buy more and more"}, {"start": 950.32, "end": 955.32, "text": " different kinds of pencils."}, {"start": 955.32, "end": 956.32, "text": " Although there may be different designs,"}, {"start": 956.32, "end": 958.32, "text": " different colours,"}, {"start": 958.32, "end": 959.32, "text": " different shapes,"}, {"start": 959.32, "end": 960.32, "text": " different sizes,"}, {"start": 960.32, "end": 962.32, "text": " ultimately what is important is,"}, {"start": 962.32, "end": 971.32, "text": " the lead inside the pencil."}, {"start": 971.32, "end": 973.32, "text": " So devotee also,"}, {"start": 973.32, "end": 975.32, "text": " what is important is not our colour,"}, {"start": 975.32, "end": 976.32, "text": " not our complexion,"}, {"start": 976.32, "end": 978.32, "text": " not our nationality,"}, {"start": 978.32, "end": 979.32, "text": " not our caste,"}, {"start": 979.32, "end": 982.32, "text": " not our creed,"}, {"start": 982.32, "end": 985.32, "text": " not how we look."}, {"start": 985.32, "end": 987.32, "text": " What is really important is,"}, {"start": 987.32, "end": 990.32, "text": " what's our consciousness?"}, {"start": 990.32, "end": 991.32, "text": " What's inside us?"}, {"start": 991.32, "end": 992.32, "text": " What's our character?"}, {"start": 992.32, "end": 996.32, "text": " What's our values?"}, {"start": 996.32, "end": 998.32, "text": " So devotee of the Lord also,"}, {"start": 998.32, "end": 999.32, "text": " see Hiranyakashipu,"}, {"start": 999.32, "end": 1001.32, "text": " he is trying to control the world outside."}, {"start": 1001.32, "end": 1004.32, "text": " He got control of three planetary systems,"}, {"start": 1004.32, "end": 1006.32, "text": " but he didn't control himself,"}, {"start": 1006.32, "end": 1007.32, "text": " his own senses,"}, {"start": 1007.32, "end": 1011.32, "text": " his own mind."}, {"start": 1011.32, "end": 1012.32, "text": " So devotee of the Lord"}, {"start": 1012.32, "end": 1013.32, "text": " is more interested,"}, {"start": 1013.32, "end": 1014.32, "text": " what profit the man"}, {"start": 1014.32, "end": 1016.32, "text": " if he wins the whole world"}, {"start": 1016.32, "end": 1020.32, "text": " but loses his own soul?"}, {"start": 1020.32, "end": 1022.32, "text": " What profit the man if he wins the whole world?"}, {"start": 1022.32, "end": 1024.3200000000002, "text": " Today actually this is the problem,"}, {"start": 1024.3200000000002, "end": 1025.3200000000002, "text": " people are very active,"}, {"start": 1025.3200000000002, "end": 1026.3200000000002, "text": " very busy,"}, {"start": 1026.3200000000002, "end": 1028.3200000000002, "text": " very passionate,"}, {"start": 1028.3200000000002, "end": 1030.3200000000002, "text": " very hardworking,"}, {"start": 1030.3200000000002, "end": 1033.3200000000002, "text": " but more is to control the world around them,"}, {"start": 1033.3200000000002, "end": 1035.3200000000002, "text": " control the environment,"}, {"start": 1035.3200000000002, "end": 1036.3200000000002, "text": " control the people,"}, {"start": 1036.3200000000002, "end": 1037.3200000000002, "text": " control situations."}, {"start": 1037.3200000000002, "end": 1041.3200000000002, "text": " But very few are wanting to control themselves."}, {"start": 1041.3200000000002, "end": 1046.3200000000002, "text": " Hiranyakashipu,"}, {"start": 1046.3200000000002, "end": 1048.3200000000002, "text": " because he was in control of his excellence,"}, {"start": 1048.32, "end": 1051.32, "text": " he thought that he is immortal,"}, {"start": 1051.32, "end": 1052.32, "text": " he is great,"}, {"start": 1052.32, "end": 1055.32, "text": " because of that he is puffed up."}, {"start": 1055.32, "end": 1056.32, "text": " A devotee of the Lord,"}, {"start": 1056.32, "end": 1060.32, "text": " realizing that Krishna is the supreme controller,"}, {"start": 1060.32, "end": 1063.32, "text": " everything is moving as per his wish,"}, {"start": 1063.32, "end": 1066.32, "text": " he doesn't get artificially puffed up,"}, {"start": 1066.32, "end": 1071.32, "text": " he is more busy in purifying his consciousness,"}, {"start": 1071.32, "end": 1073.32, "text": " in thinking of Krishna,"}, {"start": 1073.32, "end": 1075.32, "text": " remembering Krishna."}, {"start": 1075.32, "end": 1077.32, "text": " In the 18th verse in the 4th chapter,"}, {"start": 1077.32, "end": 1078.32, "text": " Krishna says,"}, {"start": 1078.32, "end": 1080.32, "text": " the one who sees action in inaction"}, {"start": 1080.32, "end": 1082.32, "text": " and inaction in action"}, {"start": 1082.32, "end": 1088.32, "text": " is intelligent among men."}, {"start": 1088.32, "end": 1090.32, "text": " A devotee may be just sitting in one place,"}, {"start": 1090.32, "end": 1091.32, "text": " chanting Krishna's name,"}, {"start": 1091.32, "end": 1092.32, "text": " remembering,"}, {"start": 1092.32, "end": 1093.32, "text": " apparently doing nothing,"}, {"start": 1093.32, "end": 1095.32, "text": " inaction,"}, {"start": 1095.32, "end": 1097.32, "text": " but that is real action."}, {"start": 1097.32, "end": 1099.32, "text": " That is real thing."}, {"start": 1099.32, "end": 1101.32, "text": " Just like in a pencil,"}, {"start": 1101.32, "end": 1102.32, "text": " the lead inside,"}, {"start": 1102.32, "end": 1104.32, "text": " the pencil may be attractive color,"}, {"start": 1104.32, "end": 1105.32, "text": " but what really matters,"}, {"start": 1105.32, "end": 1107.32, "text": " what finally you can do"}, {"start": 1107.32, "end": 1109.32, "text": " with the pencil is dependent on"}, {"start": 1109.32, "end": 1113.32, "text": " the quality of the lead inside."}, {"start": 1113.32, "end": 1116.32, "text": " So we should also not be very conscious"}, {"start": 1116.32, "end": 1120.32, "text": " of our excellence,"}, {"start": 1120.32, "end": 1123.32, "text": " we should be more conscious of our,"}, {"start": 1123.32, "end": 1126.32, "text": " what's going inside us,"}, {"start": 1126.32, "end": 1128.32, "text": " what's our consciousness."}, {"start": 1128.32, "end": 1133.32, "text": " And the fifth quality of the pencil is,"}, {"start": 1133.32, "end": 1136.32, "text": " it is conscious that everything"}, {"start": 1136.32, "end": 1138.32, "text": " will leave a mark."}, {"start": 1138.32, "end": 1141.32, "text": " When you put a pencil on a paper,"}, {"start": 1141.32, "end": 1143.32, "text": " it leaves a mark."}, {"start": 1143.32, "end": 1146.32, "text": " Likewise, our actions also leave a mark,"}, {"start": 1146.32, "end": 1147.32, "text": " good or bad."}, {"start": 1147.32, "end": 1150.32, "text": " Every action has an equal and opposite reaction,"}, {"start": 1150.32, "end": 1152.32, "text": " Newton's third law of motion."}, {"start": 1152.32, "end": 1155.32, "text": " As you sow, so shall you reap."}, {"start": 1155.32, "end": 1157.32, "text": " So let's be humble enough,"}, {"start": 1157.32, "end": 1159.32, "text": " just like Rinne Kashyapu here is puffed up,"}, {"start": 1159.32, "end": 1160.32, "text": " he's reckless,"}, {"start": 1160.32, "end": 1162.32, "text": " the way he treated Prahlad."}, {"start": 1162.32, "end": 1164.32, "text": " Where is your Lord?"}, {"start": 1164.32, "end": 1165.32, "text": " Let's always remember,"}, {"start": 1165.32, "end": 1169.32, "text": " they are the stringent laws of nature,"}, {"start": 1169.32, "end": 1171.32, "text": " and they are very stringent."}, {"start": 1171.32, "end": 1174.32, "text": " Every action we are accountable for."}, {"start": 1174.32, "end": 1176.32, "text": " So having understood this,"}, {"start": 1176.32, "end": 1179.32, "text": " we should be humble"}, {"start": 1179.32, "end": 1186.32, "text": " and act with discrimination."}, {"start": 1186.32, "end": 1188.32, "text": " Our shastras are pointing out"}, {"start": 1188.32, "end": 1189.32, "text": " what we should do,"}, {"start": 1189.32, "end": 1190.32, "text": " what we should not do,"}, {"start": 1190.32, "end": 1192.32, "text": " what we should be careful of,"}, {"start": 1192.32, "end": 1194.32, "text": " what we should avoid doing."}, {"start": 1195.32, "end": 1199.32, "text": " So knowing that every action,"}, {"start": 1199.32, "end": 1201.32, "text": " every word we speak,"}, {"start": 1201.32, "end": 1203.32, "text": " sometimes recklessly we may speak,"}, {"start": 1203.32, "end": 1204.32, "text": " we may hurt someone,"}, {"start": 1204.32, "end": 1210.32, "text": " although we may ask forgiveness,"}, {"start": 1210.32, "end": 1212.32, "text": " but the damage is done,"}, {"start": 1212.32, "end": 1214.32, "text": " just like a glass,"}, {"start": 1214.32, "end": 1216.32, "text": " if it cracks,"}, {"start": 1216.32, "end": 1218.32, "text": " although we may use quick fix,"}, {"start": 1218.32, "end": 1219.32, "text": " we may join together,"}, {"start": 1219.32, "end": 1221.32, "text": " but still the crack remains."}, {"start": 1221.32, "end": 1223.32, "text": " So now you have every word,"}, {"start": 1223.32, "end": 1224.32, "text": " every word,"}, {"start": 1224.32, "end": 1226.32, "text": " every word we speak,"}, {"start": 1226.32, "end": 1229.32, "text": " every action of ours leaves a mark."}, {"start": 1229.32, "end": 1231.32, "text": " So let's not be reckless,"}, {"start": 1231.32, "end": 1233.32, "text": " let's be very careful,"}, {"start": 1233.32, "end": 1237.32, "text": " and let's be very discriminative"}, {"start": 1237.32, "end": 1239.32, "text": " in leading our lives"}, {"start": 1239.32, "end": 1242.32, "text": " based on Krishna conscious principles."}, {"start": 1242.32, "end": 1244.32, "text": " So this Grandmother tells this Grandson"}, {"start": 1244.32, "end": 1247.32, "text": " that I would give you this pencil,"}, {"start": 1247.32, "end": 1248.32, "text": " and I wish and pray"}, {"start": 1248.32, "end": 1252.32, "text": " that you also imbibe these qualities in your life."}, {"start": 1252.32, "end": 1254.32, "text": " And while I was going,"}, {"start": 1254.32, "end": 1255.32, "text": " going through this,"}, {"start": 1255.32, "end": 1258.32, "text": " we see the exact opposite of these qualities"}, {"start": 1258.32, "end": 1261.32, "text": " in the character of Hrana Kashyapu."}, {"start": 1261.32, "end": 1266.32, "text": " And that's why he is Hrana Kashyapu."}, {"start": 1266.32, "end": 1269.32, "text": " He is not remembering there is a hand guiding him,"}, {"start": 1269.32, "end": 1271.32, "text": " he is not tolerant to pains and sorrows,"}, {"start": 1271.32, "end": 1272.32, "text": " wants to lord over,"}, {"start": 1272.32, "end": 1273.32, "text": " wants to control things,"}, {"start": 1273.32, "end": 1274.32, "text": " so that there is no pain,"}, {"start": 1274.32, "end": 1275.32, "text": " there is no trouble,"}, {"start": 1275.32, "end": 1276.32, "text": " he is immortal,"}, {"start": 1276.32, "end": 1277.32, "text": " there is no death,"}, {"start": 1277.32, "end": 1280.32, "text": " there is no old age,"}, {"start": 1280.32, "end": 1283.32, "text": " he is not willing to correct himself."}, {"start": 1283.32, "end": 1285.32, "text": " Lord Maharaj tried his best"}, {"start": 1285.32, "end": 1289.32, "text": " to give him some instructions,"}, {"start": 1289.32, "end": 1291.32, "text": " he was not willing to correct,"}, {"start": 1291.32, "end": 1294.32, "text": " he was not attentive to what's going on inside,"}, {"start": 1294.32, "end": 1297.32, "text": " he was more attentive to what is outside,"}, {"start": 1297.32, "end": 1299.32, "text": " and he was not conscious of his actions,"}, {"start": 1299.32, "end": 1301.32, "text": " he was reckless."}, {"start": 1304.32, "end": 1305.32, "text": " Now here Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 1305.32, "end": 1308.32, "text": " no matter how strong a person may be,"}, {"start": 1308.32, "end": 1310.32, "text": " just like Hrana Kashyapu,"}, {"start": 1310.32, "end": 1312.32, "text": " these are all very wonderful pastimes just to show,"}, {"start": 1313.32, "end": 1316.32, "text": " it's a Lord's plan to teach us that"}, {"start": 1316.32, "end": 1319.32, "text": " even Hrana Kashyapu was so powerful and strong,"}, {"start": 1319.32, "end": 1320.32, "text": " compared to Hrana Kashyapu,"}, {"start": 1320.32, "end": 1322.32, "text": " what we see present day,"}, {"start": 1322.32, "end": 1323.32, "text": " so called big people,"}, {"start": 1323.32, "end": 1326.32, "text": " they are nothing."}, {"start": 1326.32, "end": 1332.32, "text": " He controlled the three planetary systems,"}, {"start": 1332.32, "end": 1335.32, "text": " whereas here we see some people controlling"}, {"start": 1335.32, "end": 1338.32, "text": " a particular company or a particular state,"}, {"start": 1338.32, "end": 1341.32, "text": " a particular country."}, {"start": 1341.32, "end": 1343.32, "text": " So it was Lord's plan,"}, {"start": 1343.32, "end": 1345.32, "text": " to teach people that even Hrana Kashyapu,"}, {"start": 1345.32, "end": 1348.32, "text": " who was so powerful and strongly built,"}, {"start": 1348.32, "end": 1349.32, "text": " could not live more than his"}, {"start": 1349.32, "end": 1355.32, "text": " disdained duration of life."}, {"start": 1355.32, "end": 1358.32, "text": " One may become as strong as Prabhupada,"}, {"start": 1358.32, "end": 1359.32, "text": " as Hrana Kashyapu,"}, {"start": 1359.32, "end": 1362.32, "text": " and bring under his control all the three worlds,"}, {"start": 1362.32, "end": 1365.32, "text": " but there is no possibility of continuing his life eternally,"}, {"start": 1365.32, "end": 1372.32, "text": " or keeping the conquered booty forever."}, {"start": 1372.32, "end": 1374.32, "text": " People want to control things,"}, {"start": 1374.32, "end": 1375.32, "text": " accumulate things,"}, {"start": 1375.32, "end": 1377.32, "text": " hoard things,"}, {"start": 1377.32, "end": 1379.32, "text": " but whatever our booty,"}, {"start": 1379.32, "end": 1380.32, "text": " booty means, you know,"}, {"start": 1380.32, "end": 1381.32, "text": " when you loot something,"}, {"start": 1381.32, "end": 1385.32, "text": " that's called a booty."}, {"start": 1385.32, "end": 1386.32, "text": " Whatever the booty may be,"}, {"start": 1386.32, "end": 1389.32, "text": " whatever we have so painstakingly gathered,"}, {"start": 1389.32, "end": 1390.32, "text": " accumulated,"}, {"start": 1390.32, "end": 1397.32, "text": " we'll have to leave and go."}, {"start": 1397.32, "end": 1400.32, "text": " Just last Sunday we were discussing,"}, {"start": 1402.32, "end": 1405.32, "text": " Atal Bihari Vajpayee,"}, {"start": 1405.32, "end": 1406.32, "text": " we all have heard about him,"}, {"start": 1406.32, "end": 1408.32, "text": " he was the Prime Minister of the country,"}, {"start": 1408.32, "end": 1410.32, "text": " very charismatic Prime Minister."}, {"start": 1410.32, "end": 1413.32, "text": " He was known for his speeches."}, {"start": 1413.32, "end": 1418.32, "text": " People would get inspired by his speeches."}, {"start": 1418.32, "end": 1423.32, "text": " He was very bold, very courageous."}, {"start": 1423.32, "end": 1426.32, "text": " And when he was the Prime Minister,"}, {"start": 1426.32, "end": 1430.32, "text": " naturally headlines every day,"}, {"start": 1430.32, "end": 1431.32, "text": " whatever he is speaking,"}, {"start": 1431.32, "end": 1432.32, "text": " all his remarks,"}, {"start": 1432.32, "end": 1433.32, "text": " all his comments,"}, {"start": 1433.32, "end": 1434.32, "text": " all his views,"}, {"start": 1434.32, "end": 1435.32, "text": " all his opinions,"}, {"start": 1435.32, "end": 1437.32, "text": " all newspapers,"}, {"start": 1437.32, "end": 1439.32, "text": " all over the world,"}, {"start": 1439.32, "end": 1442.32, "text": " he was as charismatic as our present PM,"}, {"start": 1442.32, "end": 1448.32, "text": " or even more than that."}, {"start": 1448.32, "end": 1456.32, "text": " And Prime Minister is very powerful."}, {"start": 1456.32, "end": 1458.32, "text": " Today he is still alive."}, {"start": 1461.32, "end": 1466.32, "text": " But no one is talking about him."}, {"start": 1466.32, "end": 1474.32, "text": " You hardly read anything about him."}, {"start": 1474.32, "end": 1477.32, "text": " Because of old age,"}, {"start": 1477.32, "end": 1479.32, "text": " because of disease,"}, {"start": 1479.32, "end": 1481.32, "text": " he is there,"}, {"start": 1481.32, "end": 1482.32, "text": " in his place,"}, {"start": 1482.32, "end": 1483.32, "text": " in his house,"}, {"start": 1483.32, "end": 1486.32, "text": " no doubt taken care of."}, {"start": 1486.32, "end": 1490.32, "text": " He was recently awarded Bharat Ratna."}, {"start": 1490.32, "end": 1492.32, "text": " He could not come and collect the prize,"}, {"start": 1492.32, "end": 1498.32, "text": " so people went there to confer this Bharat Ratna to him."}, {"start": 1498.32, "end": 1502.32, "text": " He must be bedridden,"}, {"start": 1502.32, "end": 1503.32, "text": " cannot move,"}, {"start": 1503.32, "end": 1506.32, "text": " cannot talk,"}, {"start": 1506.32, "end": 1510.32, "text": " I am sure must be going through various pains"}, {"start": 1510.32, "end": 1512.32, "text": " which accompanies old age,"}, {"start": 1512.32, "end": 1513.32, "text": " diseases,"}, {"start": 1513.32, "end": 1515.32, "text": " invalidity,"}, {"start": 1515.32, "end": 1516.32, "text": " cannot see properly,"}, {"start": 1516.32, "end": 1518.32, "text": " cannot walk properly."}, {"start": 1520.32, "end": 1522.32, "text": " So here it is said,"}, {"start": 1522.32, "end": 1525.32, "text": " just try to imagine 10 years back,"}, {"start": 1525.32, "end": 1526.32, "text": " or 15 years back,"}, {"start": 1526.32, "end": 1530.32, "text": " he was so charismatic,"}, {"start": 1530.32, "end": 1532.32, "text": " he would come and speak and move the things,"}, {"start": 1532.32, "end": 1534.32, "text": " move the situations,"}, {"start": 1534.32, "end": 1535.32, "text": " control a lot of things,"}, {"start": 1535.32, "end": 1539.32, "text": " the whole country was practically under his..."}, {"start": 1539.32, "end": 1542.32, "text": " So many emperors have ascended to power"}, {"start": 1542.32, "end": 1544.32, "text": " and they are now lost in oblivion."}, {"start": 1544.32, "end": 1549.32, "text": " Big, big civilizations have come and gone."}, {"start": 1549.32, "end": 1551.32, "text": " In the history books,"}, {"start": 1551.32, "end": 1554.32, "text": " we read about Mesopotamian, Harappan,"}, {"start": 1554.32, "end": 1555.32, "text": " Indus Valley,"}, {"start": 1555.32, "end": 1557.32, "text": " different civilizations,"}, {"start": 1557.32, "end": 1560.32, "text": " so-called advanced civilizations have come and gone."}, {"start": 1560.32, "end": 1563.32, "text": " That is the history of the world."}, {"start": 1563.32, "end": 1564.32, "text": " People come,"}, {"start": 1564.32, "end": 1566.32, "text": " they accumulate power,"}, {"start": 1566.32, "end": 1567.32, "text": " they become puffed up,"}, {"start": 1567.32, "end": 1570.32, "text": " for a while they are in control of things,"}, {"start": 1570.32, "end": 1573.32, "text": " they feel that they are the Lord,"}, {"start": 1573.32, "end": 1575.32, "text": " and then Kala comes,"}, {"start": 1575.32, "end": 1577.32, "text": " a wave of Kala comes,"}, {"start": 1577.32, "end": 1579.32, "text": " and it's lost in oblivion."}, {"start": 1579.32, "end": 1583.32, "text": " People don't even remember."}, {"start": 1583.32, "end": 1586.32, "text": " It's a very critical, classic case."}, {"start": 1586.32, "end": 1588.32, "text": " Prime Minister of the country,"}, {"start": 1588.32, "end": 1591.32, "text": " we don't even hear of him these days."}, {"start": 1591.32, "end": 1595.32, "text": " He's still alive."}, {"start": 1595.32, "end": 1597.32, "text": " So, devotee of the Lord,"}, {"start": 1597.32, "end": 1599.32, "text": " it is not that when we become devotees,"}, {"start": 1599.32, "end": 1600.32, "text": " just like here it says,"}, {"start": 1600.32, "end": 1604.32, "text": " no one is free from the principles of material existence,"}, {"start": 1604.32, "end": 1606.32, "text": " four principles of material existence,"}, {"start": 1606.32, "end": 1608.32, "text": " namely birth, death, old age and disease."}, {"start": 1609.32, "end": 1612.32, "text": " It is not that when we become devotees also,"}, {"start": 1612.32, "end": 1614.32, "text": " we'll get freed from this."}, {"start": 1614.32, "end": 1617.32, "text": " A devotee also gets disease."}, {"start": 1617.32, "end": 1619.32, "text": " A devotee also becomes old."}, {"start": 1619.32, "end": 1622.32, "text": " A devotee also dies."}, {"start": 1622.32, "end": 1626.32, "text": " But, because of the consciousness,"}, {"start": 1626.32, "end": 1627.32, "text": " Krishna consciousness,"}, {"start": 1627.32, "end": 1628.32, "text": " he goes through,"}, {"start": 1628.32, "end": 1631.32, "text": " just like the pencil example allows,"}, {"start": 1631.32, "end": 1635.32, "text": " a devotee goes through all this material existence,"}, {"start": 1635.32, "end": 1638.32, "text": " but all these things intensify his,"}, {"start": 1638.32, "end": 1641.32, "text": " dependence on Krishna."}, {"start": 1641.32, "end": 1643.32, "text": " So, Prabhupada says,"}, {"start": 1643.32, "end": 1645.32, "text": " even during the presence of Krishna,"}, {"start": 1645.32, "end": 1647.32, "text": " when Nanda Maharaj and other kahud men"}, {"start": 1647.32, "end": 1650.32, "text": " had the Supreme Personality of Godhead in their presence,"}, {"start": 1650.32, "end": 1655.32, "text": " there were disturbances."}, {"start": 1655.32, "end": 1656.32, "text": " So, devotee of the Lord,"}, {"start": 1656.32, "end": 1658.32, "text": " he is not,"}, {"start": 1658.32, "end": 1659.32, "text": " he is not,"}, {"start": 1659.32, "end": 1660.32, "text": " because of his knowledge,"}, {"start": 1660.32, "end": 1663.32, "text": " because of his consciousness,"}, {"start": 1663.32, "end": 1666.32, "text": " he is not having a false hope that,"}, {"start": 1666.32, "end": 1667.32, "text": " now because I am a devotee,"}, {"start": 1667.32, "end": 1668.32, "text": " Krishna is protecting me,"}, {"start": 1668.32, "end": 1672.32, "text": " so I don't have to go through all that."}, {"start": 1672.32, "end": 1674.32, "text": " Disturbances will come."}, {"start": 1674.32, "end": 1676.32, "text": " tam titikshu sabharata"}, {"start": 1676.32, "end": 1678.32, "text": " Learn to tolerate without being disturbed."}]}